{
  "texts": [
    "Our model also replicates data from Bosking et al.",
    "71 who examined phosphene size as a function of eccentricity for 93 surface electrodes (0.25 mm radius) implanted in 13 patients.",
    "Figure 5B replots estimates of phosphene size based on patient drawings, with the dashed line showing the best linear fit, (r(41) = 0.884, p < 0.0001).",
    "Figure 5C shows simulated predictions for these same eccentricities, along with replotting the best linear fit to the Bosking et al. patient data.",
    "The upper curve (triangles) in Figure 5C represents estimates based on a metaanalysis 67 of five older published studies in cebus, owl and macaque monkeys [73] [74] [75] [76] [77]."
  ]
}